<MELItem itemNbr="27-61-03" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-27-61-03.1.2-27-61-03">
<Title>Automatic Speedbrake Function</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="1" nbrRequired="0" opsIndicator="(O)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Speedbrake lever position transducers operate normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>ARMED detent is not used.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Appropriate performance adjustments are applied.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
<Note>
<Para>Use Boeing Onboard Performance Tool (OPT) to determine take-off weight and/or landing weight as it affects aircraft performance.</Para>
</Note>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<OperationProcedure>
<Note>
<Para>AUTO SPEEDBRAKE advisory message may remain displayed.</Para>
</Note>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Base takeoff and landing performance on manual speedbrakes. Use On-board Performance Tool (OPT) to apply the appropriate take-off performance penalties.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Do not use the ARMED detent.  </Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Extend speedbrakes manually for rejected takeoff or landing.</Para>
<List listType="A.">
<ListItem>
<Para>For rejected takeoff:</Para>
<List listType="1)">
<ListItem>
<Para>Simultaneously close the thrust levers, disengage the autothrottles and apply maximum manual wheel brakes or verify operation of RTO autobrakes.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Manually raise SPEED BRAKE lever.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Apply the maximum amount of reverse thrust consistent with conditions.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>For landing, use AUTO SPEEDBRAKE non-normal checklist.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Maximum landing capability is CAT I.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</OperationProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
</DispatchItems>